This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:59 PM Prosecuting attorney Chad C La Lor in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Keith Norman Swanson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Ellen Denise Craker makes a special appearance and appears by video for Keith Norman Swanson. Defendant's address confirmed. Attorney/Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint, waives a formal reading, and requests a preliminary hearing. State asks for $2500 cash. No contact with Victim 1, her family, or The Boardroom Bar. No use or possession of alcohol. Defendant does not have significant history, only traffic infractions in MN but cites severity of charges alleged. No FTAs in the files. Court indicates concerns over no contact with family condition. State does not have specific names of family members.  Attorney Craker reviews defendant's history, has ties to the community and employment in the area. Asks for high signature bond, defendant can post up to $500. 

Court orders $2500 cash. No contact with Victim 1or The Boardroom Bar. No use or possession of alcohol. 
Defendant waives time limits of preliminary to allow time to retain counsel. Court accepts waiver as knowingly and voluntarily made.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 20, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Status conference scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
